The paper deals with load balancing in geographically-distributed systems, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and computer networks (cs.NI). The algorithms presented in the paper are designed to optimize the load balancing process, which involves decision-making and optimization, making it relevant to systems and control (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses load functions, which are mathematical models used to describe the behavior of servers under load, making it relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
